 Passing motorists only noticed the man leaning against the slope of the offramp, at first light. Jana Boshoff, who was travelling to Johannesburg that morning, said that she initially thought the man was sleeping next to the road, but then noticed blood pooling at his feet. She did not want to stop due to safety concerns and alerted Trac Assist. Passersby also informed operators at the Middelburg Toll Gate of the man lying next to the road. They presumed that he was dead. When ER24 medics arrived at the scene, the man was found to still be alive. He was rushed to the Middelburg Provincial Hospital with serious injuries. It is presumend that the man was struck by a vehicle, who failed to stop, before sunrise.     Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation Botshabelo’s last song Five busted for dagga Nabbed cops granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za